### Saturday 16 May RACE DAY
> Fuel: Race Day Protocol
- 2 to 3 hours before: 3g/kg = ~210g carbs (50-60g HBCDs in 500ml water + ~120-130g cream of rice with banana + Nutella, OR 4-5 rice cakes with Nutella + banana + dates)
- 30 min before: 1 Roctane gel + sip water
- Warm-up (12 to 15): jump rope 90 sec + easy jog + drills + 3 strides
- First 15 to 20 min controlled, no surge — stay low Zone 3, resist the pack
- Flat/riverside sections: 5:30 to 5:45/km in low Zone 3
- Climbs/forest sections: accept Zone 4 HR, use quick-feet downhill to recover
- Before technical obstacles (Spear Throw, Multi-Rig): pause 5 to 10 sec, lower HR, breathe, then execute
- Running pace target: 5:30 to 5:45/km on flat/trail sections to bank time for obstacles
- Overall average target: 6:00/km including obstacles (3 hours for 30 km)
- Fuel: 1 Roctane gel every 20 to 25 min from 20 min in + sip carb drink mix between gels — target 80 to 90g carbs/hr
- Electrolytes: 1 cap every 25 to 30 min throughout
- Fuel and pace exactly like Saturday rehearsals — no surprises on race day

